gomodel:SYNGO_1038  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The paper demonstrates that an abundant signal for catenin delta can be detected in purified PSD fractions from rat brain using WB (Fig 1b).\n\nFigure 3 shows that delta-Catenin interacts with glutamate receptor complexes in brain. A WB signal for delta-Catenin can be found in IP fractions of PSD95, MgluR1alpha and NR2A (3A). The receptors can be detected in a delta-catenin IP sample (3B-D).\n\n21/8/2017 Pim\n- Via PMID:9971746 the annotated gene was traced to rat CTNND2 (compared peptide sequences shown in Fig.1 PEPAPPPPPPP and KKKKKKK). Experimental description: For the fractionation of PSD, rat brain homogenates were produced and the crude synaptosomes P2 was isolated as described" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" ;
        dc:date           "2017-08-21" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1038" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

